name: Amir Abdur-Rahim
summary: Amir Abdur-Rahim, head coach of the University of South Florida men's basketball team, has sadly passed away at the age of 43. Tributes have poured in from the sports community, including ESPN, NBC Miami, and USA Today. Abdur-Rahim's former employer, Kennesaw State University, also mourned his loss. name: Crane
summary: A crane collapsed during Hurricane Milton, but authorities are not investigating the incident. Meanwhile, in Minnesota and Wisconsin, the massive sandhill crane migration is underway. In New York City's Madison Square Park, a defunct crane remains a puzzling fixture. Stephen Morris, a resident of Ohio, passed away in 2024. The Bob Crane Community Center is seeking applicants for employment opportunities. At the Naval Surface Warfare Center Crane Division, an enlisted certification program for electromagnetic warfare technology has been implemented. Jeremiah Crane serves on the Boulder Daily Camera's Board of Trustees. On the radio, Arcadia Grey's "Origami Crane" is featured. Former Navajo Nation President Russell Begaye challenges Republican candidate Eli Crane in the Arizona gubernatorial race. Brandon Da Costa has been a standout player for the Ichabod Crane boys' soccer team.
